'''David Miles Hogg''' (born April 12, 2000) is an American [[gun violence in the United States|gun control]] activist and politician, serving as vice chair of the [[Democratic National Committee]] since 2025.<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/donald-trump/live-blog/trump-administration-tariffs-canada-china-mexico-live-updates-rcna190143/rcrd71801 |title=David Hogg elected vice chair of the DNC}}</ref> He rose to prominence during the [[2018 United States gun violence protests]] as a student survivor of the [[Parkland high school shooting|Stoneman Douglas High School shooting]], helping lead several high-profile protests, marches, and boycotts, including the [[boycott of The Ingraham Angle|boycott of ''The Ingraham Angle'']].<ref>{{cite news|title=Student reporter interviews classmates hiding from gunman in Florida high school|url=http://www.miamiherald.com/news/local/community/broward/article200277689.html|access-date=February 25, 2018|work=[[The Miami Herald]]|date=February 15, 2018|format=video|archive-date=April 1, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401195443/https://www.miamiherald.com/news/local/community/broward/article200277689.html|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Prusher150218">{{cite news|last1=Prusher|first1=Ilene|title=A Student Started Filming During the Florida School Shooting. He Hasn't Stopped|url=https://time.com/5161034/florida-school-shooting-survivor/|access-date=February 21, 2018|magazine=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|date=February 15, 2018|archive-date=April 21, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190421041942/http://time.com/5161034/florida-school-shooting-survivor/|url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Kir200218">{{cite news|last1=Kirby|first1=Jen|title=Florida shooting survivor explains how his generation can force a change on guns|url=https://www.vox.com/policy-and-politics/2018/2/20/17030294/florida-shooting-survivor-david-hogg-gun-control|access-date=February 21, 2018|publisher=[[Vox (website)|Vox]]|d